data.value:
1. Click "File" → "Select File" to select the local file you want to look for (if the file path is set in Location, you do not need to select the file).
2. There are two ways to express location information in this project: 1) Regular Expression: Click "Option" → "Regular Expression". When the location information is verified by the regular expression, the desired content will be displayed. 2) XML: Click "Option" → "XML", when the location information is verified by the.xsd file, the content you want to find pops up.
3. Click "About" → "Help" to to view the help guide.
4. Click "About" → "Others" to find out who owns the software and what version it is.
